The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of deep learning models on Natural Language Inference (NLI) and Sentiment Analysis (SA) tasks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The use of psychometric methods to model difficulty also suggests a focus on human cognition and perception, which is relevant to these sub-categories.
